<section>
  <title>Small Dataset</title>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small">
    <title>Question 1 - Small Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You're working intensively with a small group of farmers.
    </p>
        <image source="images/aminou_question.png" width="70%">
          <description>A farmer approaching Aminou during intensive trial work, having observed the results firsthand, asking about variety selection</description>
        </image>
    <p>
      One morning, a farmer approaches you. <q>Aminou, I've been watching the trials. What variety should I plant next season - ICRI or Locale?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You pause. Across Ilam, Regin, and Anikrub, thousands of plots were studied. Farmers tried two varieties: ICRI and Locale.
    </p>

    <p>
      You have detailed data from this group, collected with care. So you sit down with them to give them some advice. What do you say?
    </p>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-icri">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-locale">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-either">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-idk">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small-icri">
    <title>ICRI - Small Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You nod confidently, <q>Plant ICRI.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer squints at you, <q>Hmm.</q> They're not convinced, and that plays on your mind.
    </p>

    <p>
      Later that evening, as you sit reviewing the data more carefully, something unsettles you.
    </p>

    <p>
      <q>Wait<ellipsis/> what?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You flip back through your tables.
    </p>

    <p>
      You would have expected that pattern somewhere else -- but do you expect that here in Anikrub?
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer comes back the next day.
    </p>

    <p>
      <q>So<ellipsis/> are you sure?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      What do you say now?
    </p>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-icri-icri">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-icri-either">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-icri-idk">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small-icri-icri">
    <title>ICRI Again - Small Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You double down, <q>Still ICRI.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer raises an eyebrow, <q>Do you work for this ICRI variety or something?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You feel your face warm. That Anikrub sun is hot today.
    </p>

    <p>
      Time to slow down.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        Hint: Have you looked at yield by region and variety?
      </p>
      <p>
        Not just overall yield - but yield broken down by region as well as variety.
      </p>
      <p>
        The data are not flat, they are layered. Try again.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small-icri-either">
    <title>Either - Small Dataset (After ICRI)</title>
    
    <p>
      <q>Either one should be fine.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer frowns, <q>That doesn't sound very confident.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The Anikrub sun is hot and you feel sweat going down your face. You realise you may be smoothing over something important.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        Hint: Look at yield by region and variety. Averages across countries can hide regional differences.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small-icri-idk">
    <title>I Don't Know - Small Dataset (After ICRI)</title>
    
    <p>
      You hesitate. <q>I<ellipsis/> need to check something.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You reopen your analysis.
    </p>

    <p>
      You suddenly notice that you've been looking at overall averages across all three countries.
    </p>

    <p>
      But this farmer is in <alert>Anikrub</alert>, and the pattern here is not the same as the overall pattern from your data.
    </p>

    <assemblage>
      <p>
        Hint:
      </p>
      <p>
        Filter the data to Anikrub.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then compare yield by variety.
      </p>
    </assemblage>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-locale-correct">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small-icri-locale">

    <title>Correcting to Locale - Small Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      Yes, Locale is the right recommendation for Anikrub.
    </p>

    <p>
      You've just experienced <alert>Simpson's Paradox</alert> again.
    </p>

    <p>
      In this case:
      <ul>
        <li><p>Overall, ICRI might have looked better on average.</p></li>
        <li><p>But in Anikrub specifically, Locale performs better.</p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>

    <p>
      The key lesson: <alert>Always check the context</alert>. Aggregate statistics can mislead when there are meaningful subgroups.
    </p>

    <p>
      Continue to <xref ref="Q2-small">Question 2</xref>.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small-locale-correct">
    <title>Locale - Anikrub (Correct)</title>
    
    <p>
      You smile. <q>For Anikrub? Plant the Local variety.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer nods slowly. <q>That makes sense. It's what many of us have been noticing.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You feel relieved -- and slightly humbled.
    </p>

    <p>
      Across the entire dataset, ICRI may look stronger on average. But when you break the data down by region, Anikrub tells a different story.
    </p>

    <p>
      You've just discovered something important:
    </p>

    <p>
      Overall averages can mislead and the best decision can depend on context.
    </p>

    <p>
      You turn the page in your notebook. This is more complicated than you thought.
    </p>

    <p>
      Continue to <xref ref="Q2-small">Question 2</xref>.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small-locale">
    <title>Locale - Small Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You say confidently, <q>Locale.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer smiles. <q>Interesting. That matches what some of us have seen.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      But then he tilts his head. <q>If you're so sure<ellipsis/> tell me this. In which region does Local outperform ICRI on average?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      Now it's your turn to think.
    </p>

    <p>
      <alert>Option:</alert>
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-icri-regin">Regin</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-icri-ilam">Ilam</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-locale-correct">Anikrub</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-icri-idk">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs xml:id="Q1-small-either">
    <title>Either - Small Dataset</title>
    
    <p>
      You pause.
    </p>

    <p>
      <q>Either one.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer narrows his eyes.
    </p>

    <p>
      <q>Either?</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      He shifts his weight. <q>We're in Anikrub, you know.</q>
    </p>

    <p>
      You feel that small tightening in your stomach.
    </p>

    <p>
      With a larger dataset, you had thousands of farmers across all three countries. Patterns would be clearer – even if misleading at first glance.
    </p>

    <p>
      But this time, you're working with several hundred farmers. Carefully sampled. Balanced. Manageable.
    </p>

    <p>
      But not enormous.
    </p>

    <p>
      You pull out your notebook again.
    </p>

    <p>
      Across the dataset, the overall difference between ICRI and Local is<ellipsis/> small.
    </p>

    <p>
      Very small.
    </p>

    <p>
      When you look at Anikrub alone, the pattern seems to shift slightly.
    </p>

    <p>
      But is that shift real?
    </p>

    <p>
      Or is it noise?
    </p>

    <p>
      You stare at the numbers. Does knowing this farmer is from Anikrub change your answer?
    </p>

    <p>
      The farmer waits.
    </p>

    <p>
      What do you say?
      <ul>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-icri">ICRI</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-locale">Locale</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-help">Either</xref></p></li>
        <li><p><xref ref="Q1-small-idk">I don't know</xref></p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>


